ENTRY            F0928   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0928001   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  7         14
TITLE      A study of some 3He induced reactions on 13C and the
           structure of 16O
AUTHOR     (H.R.Weller,N.R.Roberson,D.R.Tilley)
INSTITUTE  (1USADKE,1USANCS)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,122,529,1968)
           #doi:10.1016/0375-9474(68)90575-7
FACILITY   (VDG,1USADKE) 4 MeV Van de Graaff accelerator.
INC-SOURCE The doubly ionized 3He beam was used which provided
           0.2 mu-A of 3He particles on target with energies up
           to 8.2 MeV.
HISTORY    (20080425C)
           (20100217A) Correction was made in the AUTHOR record.
           (20230126A) Corrections were done in Sub 007, 008.
           (20251227U) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              14
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           17
SUBENT        F0928002   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  8         15
REACTION   (6-C-13(HE3,A)6-C-12,PAR,DA)
MONITOR    (6-C-13(HE3,A)6-C-12,PAR,DA)
MONIT-REF  (,H.D.Holmgren,J,PR,106,100,1957)
SAMPLE     (6-C-13,ENR=0.60) The technique of cracking 60%
           enriched 13C methyl iodide on a thin nickel foil and
           dissolving the foil in acid was used to obtain
           self-supporting targets of about 75 ug/cm2 thickness.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Four 300 um surface barrier detectors
           mounted in a 30 cm scattering chamber were used.
ERR-ANALYS Carbon build-up on the target introduced an uncertainty
           in the percentage of 13C in the target and resulted in
           an over-all error of approximately 50%
           (ERR-S) Statistical error
STATUS     (CURVE,,H.R.Weller+,J,NP/A,122,529,1968) Figs 3-5,18
HISTORY    (20251227U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB              15
COMMON               2          3
ANG-ERR-D  ERR-DIG
ADEG       PER-CENT
       0.14        0.2
ENDCOMMON            3
