ENDSUBENT          602
SUBENT        F0928003   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  6         15
REACTION   (6-C-13(HE3,A)6-C-12,PAR,DA,,REL)
            No information about units.
SAMPLE     (6-C-13,ENR=0.60) The technique of cracking 60%
           enriched 13C methyl iodide on a thin nickel foil and
           dissolving the foil in acid was used to obtain
           self-supporting targets of about 75 ug/cm2 thickness.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Four 300 um surface barrier detectors
           mounted in a 30 cm scattering chamber were used.
ERR-ANALYS Carbon build-up on the target introduced an uncertainty
           in the percentage of 13C in the target and resulted in
           an over-all error of approximately 50%
           (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (CURVE,,H.R.Weller+,J,NP/A,122,529,1968) Figs 6,11,12
HISTORY    (20251227A) SD: BIB updated. Data from fig.6 were
           digitized and added.
ENDBIB              15
COMMON               2          3
EN-ERR-DIG ERR-DIG
MEV        ARB-UNITS
 0.001             0.7
ENDCOMMON            3
